 The Study to Treat Superficial Femoral Artery Occlusions.

@highlight

The main objective of this study is to assess the performance of the Cordis SMART cent nitinol self-expandable stent for the treatment of superficial femoral artery (SFA) occlusions in comparison with balloon angioplasty only as determined by binary restenosis at one year.

